{
  "text": "Environmental complexification allows to more continuously change the complexity of the task through the tuning of dedicated parameters. Gomez et al. [CITATION_1] thus worked on a prey-capture task parameterized with the prey speed and the delay before starting the pursuit. Ten ordered sub-tasks were thus defined by specific values of these parameters and their use proved to lead to more efficient solutions.",
  "citation_candidates": [
